    <string name="about_changelog"><b>Release Notes</b>	\n0.55
	\n - fixed bug in MessageBuilder. Flags were converted to numbers in some cases.
	\n0.53
	\n - fixed bug in Amarino API (in Amarino.java), device address was not sent when using sendDataToArduino() function
	\n\n0.52
	\n - added fall back when UUID does not work, it will try to use the good old port 1
	\n\n0.5
	\n - uses UUID (instead of always port 1) to determine which port to use when connecting to a Bluetooth module
	\n - added release notes dialog to show up when a new Amarino version has been installed
	\n - shows a message when no plug-ins are installed and user tries to add an event</string>
    <string name="about_msg">Amarino 2.0 - A prototyping platform for Android and Arduino
	\n\n\u00A9 2010 by Bonifaz Kaufmann
	\n\nhttp://www.amarino-toolkit.net
	
	\n\nThanks to Stefano Sanna and Emanuele Di Saverio, since Amarino uses
	their Android Bluetooth API which can be found at
	\nhttp://code.google.com/p/android-bluetooth/</string>
